01:19:57,120 --> 01:20:00,480 
I know you're a cop. What do you want?
Have I done something wrong?

979
01:20:00,800 --> 01:20:03,120 
I don't know, something bad, maybe.

980
01:20:04,480 --> 01:20:06,800 
Look, why are you asking me?
I can't remember what Ive done.

981
01:20:06,880 --> 01:20:08,880 
You wouldn't believe me anyway.

982
01:20:09,000 --> 01:20:11,800 
Because of my condition, you don't
believe someone with this condition.

983
01:20:11,880 --> 01:20:14,480 
Nobody believed Sammy!
I didn't even fucking believe Sammy!

984
01:20:15,320 --> 01:20:17,200 
Ferdy's bar.

985
01:20:19,320 --> 01:20:21,680 
Come by after. Natalie.

986
01:20:36,000 --> 01:20:37,880 
- A beer, please.
- What do you want?

987
01:20:38,000 --> 01:20:38,880 
A beer, please.

988
01:20:39,000 --> 01:20:41,320 
You can't just waltz in here
dressed like that and ask for a beer.

989
01:20:41,400 --> 01:20:43,680 
- What, is there a dress code?
- Why are you here?

990
01:20:43,800 --> 01:20:46,600 
- Im meeting someone called Natalie.
- Well, that's me.

991
01:20:46,680 --> 01:20:49,320 
Yeah, we met before, right?

992
01:20:50,120 --> 01:20:52,320 
- Then why am I here?
- I don't know, why don't you tell me?

993
01:20:52,400 --> 01:20:54,320 
I don't remember.
I have no short-term memory.

994
01:20:54,400 --> 01:20:56,120 
Oh, you're that memory guy.

995
01:20:56,200 --> 01:20:59,800 
- How do you know about me?
- My boyfriend told me about you.

996
01:20:59,880 --> 01:21:03,600 
- Oh, yeah? Who's your boyfriend?
- Jimmy Grants. Do you know him?

997
01:21:04,800 --> 01:21:06,120 
No.

998
01:21:06,200 --> 01:21:11,400 
He knows you. He told me about you.
He said you were staying at the Discount.

999
01:21:11,400 --> 01:21:14,600 
In fact, a cop came by earlier
and was looking for you.

1000
01:21:14,680 --> 01:21:16,680 
Said he was looking for a guy
who can't remember anything,...

1001
01:21:16,800 --> 01:21:18,680 
..wouldn't know how he'd got here
or what he'd done.

1002
01:21:18,800 --> 01:21:20,680 
I get a lot of guys round here like that.

1003
01:21:20,800 --> 01:21:25,000 
Chronic alcoholism
is one cause of short-term memory loss.

1004
01:21:26,680 --> 01:21:29,600 
- Are you Teddy?
- No, my name's Leonard.

1005
01:21:29,680 --> 01:21:31,680 
- Did Teddy send you?
- I don't know.

1006
01:21:32,400 --> 01:21:34,320 
What's happened to Jimmy?

1007
01:21:34,400 --> 01:21:37,880 
- I don't know that, either. Sorry.
- You don't remember anything?

1008
01:21:38,000 --> 01:21:41,520 
You don't remember where you've been
or what you've just done?

1009
01:21:41,600 --> 01:21:44,880 
I can't make new memories.
Everything just fades.

1010
01:21:45,000 --> 01:21:47,680 
- Then why did you come here?
- I found this in my pocket.

1011
01:21:50,800 --> 01:21:52,880 
Your pocket?

1012
01:22:07,520 --> 01:22:08,800 
(man hawks)

1013
01:22:16,200 --> 01:22:18,880 
Bar bet. Care to contribute?

1014
01:22:19,000 --> 01:22:21,400 
- No, thanks.
- Its for a lot of money.

1015
01:22:21,800 --> 01:22:25,520 
Come on. Proceeds are going to charity.
Help me out.

1016
01:22:30,600 --> 01:22:32,480 
(hawks)

1017
01:22:36,400 --> 01:22:38,120 
Thank you.

1018
01:22:54,400 --> 01:22:57,320 
- On the house.
- Thanks.

1019
01:22:58,200 --> 01:23:00,120 
(man laughs)

1020
01:23:01,000 --> 01:23:04,400 
Its completely fucked
because nobody believes you.

1021
01:23:04,400 --> 01:23:08,000 
Its amazing what a little brain damage
will do for your credibility.

1022
01:23:08,120 --> 01:23:10,320 
I guess it's poetic justice
for not believing Sammy.

1023
01:23:10,400 --> 01:23:15,000 
You know the truth about my condition,
officer? You don't know anything.

1024
01:23:15,120 --> 01:23:19,880 
You feel angry, you don't know why.
You feel guilty, you have no idea why.

1025
01:23:20,000 --> 01:23:23,400 
You could do anything and not have
the faintest idea ten minutes later.

1026
01:23:23,520 --> 01:23:26,320 
Like Sammy.
What if I'd done something like Sammy?

1027
01:23:26,400 --> 01:23:30,200 
I didn't tell you?
What happened to Sammy and his wife?

1028
01:23:30,320 --> 01:23:32,320 
She came to see me at my office.

1029
01:23:32,400 --> 01:23:37,120 
I didn't tell her what I really thought
but I never said that he was faking.

1030
01:23:37,200 --> 01:23:39,320 
Just that his condition was mental,
not physical.

1031
01:23:39,400 --> 01:23:41,880 
I found out later that she went home
and gave Sammy his final exam.

1032
01:23:43,680 --> 01:23:46,400 
Sammy? Its time for my shot.

1033
01:24:01,800 --> 01:24:04,680 
She knew beyond a doubt
that he loved her,

1034
01:24:04,800 --> 01:24:07,400 
so she found a way to test him.

1035
01:24:18,880 --> 01:24:22,320 
Sammy? Its time for my shot.

1036
01:24:23,320 --> 01:24:25,200 
Hmm.

1037
01:24:32,200 --> 01:24:35,800 
- She really thought she'd call his bluff.
- There you go.

1038
01:24:35,880 --> 01:24:40,400 
Or she just didn't want to live with
the things she'd put him through.

1039
01:24:48,800 --> 01:24:50,120 
Sammy?

1040
01:24:52,200 --> 01:24:53,600 
Its time for my shot.

1041
01:24:59,520 --> 01:25:01,200 
It won't hurt.

1042
01:25:43,320 --> 01:25:46,400 
She went into a coma
and never recovered.

1043
01:25:46,480 --> 01:25:49,600 
Sammy couldn't understand
or explain what happened.

1044
01:25:49,680 --> 01:25:50,680 
Oh!

1045
01:25:51,800 --> 01:25:56,000 
He's been in a home ever since.
He doesn't even know his wife is dead.

1046
01:25:56,120 --> 01:25:59,320 
I was wrong about Sammy
and I was wrong about his wife.

1047
01:25:59,400 --> 01:26:03,400 
She wasn't interested in the money.
She needed to understand his problem.

1048
01:26:03,520 --> 01:26:07,120 
His brain didn't respond to conditioning
but he wasn't a con man.

1049
01:26:07,200 --> 01:26:10,400 
And when she looked into his eyes,
she thought he could be the same person.

1050
01:26:10,480 --> 01:26:12,480 
When I looked into his eyes,
I thought I saw recognition.

1051
01:26:12,600 --> 01:26:14,480 
Now I know you fake it.

1052
01:26:14,600 --> 01:26:17,600 
lf you think you're supposed to recognize
somebody, you pretend to.

1053
01:26:17,680 --> 01:26:21,120 
You bluff it to get a pat on the head
from the doctors.

1054
01:26:21,200 --> 01:26:24,120 
You bluff it to seem less of a freak.

1055
01:26:25,800 --> 01:26:27,680 
What drug dealer?

1056
01:26:28,480 --> 01:26:30,480 
(tires squeal)

1057
01:26:52,320 --> 01:26:55,320 
- Hey, Lenny, how you doing?
- Its private back here.

1058
01:26:55,400 --> 01:26:58,320 
- Its OK, we know each other. Right, kid?
- How did you know I was in here?

1059
01:26:58,400 --> 01:27:00,320 
The Jag's out front.

1060
01:27:00,400 --> 01:27:03,200 
What are you still doing here, Lenny?
There's plenty of tattoo parlors up north.

1061
01:27:03,320 --> 01:27:06,680 
I guess I wanted to get something down
before it slipped my mind.

1062
01:27:06,800 --> 01:27:08,600 
- Give me the keys, Ill move it.
- It'll be all right.

1063
01:27:08,680 --> 01:27:10,680 
- Wait out there.
- Oh, for Christ...

1064
01:27:10,800 --> 01:27:12,800 
Give me a minute,
Ive got to get something for you.

1065
01:27:17,200 --> 01:27:20,600 
Fact six. Car license SG13 7lU.

1066
01:27:26,680 --> 01:27:29,680 
Look, wait a minute, will ya?

1067
01:27:32,200 --> 01:27:34,400 
- We gotta get you out of here.
- Why?

1068
01:27:34,480 --> 01:27:37,320 
Oh, man. Come on, Leonard.
How many times I gotta tell you?

1069
01:27:37,400 --> 01:27:39,800 
- Its not safe for you to hang around.
- Why not?

1070
01:27:39,880 --> 01:27:43,120 
Because that cop's looking for you.
I gotta get you a new identity,...

1071
01:27:43,200 --> 01:27:46,400 
..some new clothes, a different car
would do for now. Put these on.

1072
01:27:46,480 --> 01:27:48,320 
Whoa, whoa. What cop?

1073
01:27:48,400 --> 01:27:52,320 
He's a bad cop. He's the one
that checked you into the Discount Inn.

1074
01:27:52,400 --> 01:27:56,120 
He's been calling you for days, slipping
envelopes under your door, shit like that.

1075
01:27:56,200 --> 01:28:00,000 
- How do you know this?
- He told me. He's been laughing at you.

1076
01:28:00,120 --> 01:28:01,520 
- You're full of shit.
- No, Im not.

1077
01:28:01,600 --> 01:28:03,520 
He knows you're no good on the phone
so he's been calling you up.

1078
01:28:03,600 --> 01:28:05,520 
Sometimes you don't answer the phone...

1079
01:28:05,600 --> 01:28:08,320 
..so he slips shit under your door
to scare you into answering it,...

1080
01:28:08,400 --> 01:28:13,320 
..giving you a line of crap about John G
being a local drug dealer. Jimmy Grants.

1081
01:28:13,400 --> 01:28:16,120 
- Who's Jimmy Grants?
- Leonard, Jimmy's the drug dealer.

1082
01:28:16,200 --> 01:28:19,520 
The cop wants to know how his operation
is run. He's got some score in mind.

1083
01:28:19,600 --> 01:28:22,000 
- Somehow you're involved.
- How do you know him?

1084
01:28:22,120 --> 01:28:27,520 
Im a snitch. He's a cop from out of town.
The local boys put us together.

1085
01:28:27,680 --> 01:28:29,880 
lf he knew I was helping you,
he'd fucking kill me.

1086
01:28:30,000 --> 01:28:33,600 
So take these clothes, put them on
and get the fuck out of here.

1087
01:28:33,680 --> 01:28:35,520 
Come on, Leonard, just go.

1088
01:28:55,000 --> 01:28:56,800 
You are full of shit.

1089
01:28:59,600 --> 01:29:01,520 
Come by after. Natalie.

1090
01:29:02,200 --> 01:29:04,000 
Ferdy's bar.

1091
01:29:42,800 --> 01:29:44,120 
(knocks on window)

1092
01:29:44,200 --> 01:29:46,320 
Hey, Jimmy.

1093
01:29:47,800 --> 01:29:50,800 
Im sorry, I, uh,
thought you were somebody else.

1094
01:29:51,200 --> 01:29:52,880 
Sorry.

1095
01:29:53,000 --> 01:29:55,000 
That's OK.

1096
01:30:08,200 --> 01:30:12,120 
This Jimmy Grants deals drugs
out of the bar where his girlfriend works?

1097
01:30:12,400 --> 01:30:16,000 
But he's not going to bring her along?
He'll come by himself, right?

1098
01:30:16,120 --> 01:30:19,800 
I always figured the drugs angle
would be the best way to get him.

1099
01:30:20,000 --> 01:30:23,320 
No, officer. Im as ready as Ill ever be.

1100
01:30:23,400 --> 01:30:26,200 
You're in the lobby?
What do you look like?

1101
01:30:27,400 --> 01:30:28,320 
Ill be right there.

1102
01:31:09,680 --> 01:31:10,600 
Lenny!

1103
01:31:12,800 --> 01:31:14,680 
Officer Gammell?

1104
01:31:17,600 --> 01:31:19,520 
Yeah. Come on.

1105
01:31:35,600 --> 01:31:38,480 
- Hey, smile.
- Oh, don't, uh... Not here.

1106
01:31:39,320 --> 01:31:41,200 
Over here.

1107
01:31:45,600 --> 01:31:48,120 
Is it Officer or Lieutenant Gammell?

1108
01:31:48,200 --> 01:31:51,120 
You know what?
Don't write Gammell, just Teddy.

1109
01:31:51,200 --> 01:31:53,680 
- Why?
- Im undercover.

1110
01:31:56,320 --> 01:31:58,880 
This is the directions, where he's going.

1111
01:31:59,000 --> 01:32:01,680 
- My number's on the bottom if you...
- You're not coming?

1112
01:32:01,800 --> 01:32:04,480 
Nah, it wouldn't be appropriate.

1113
01:32:08,320 --> 01:32:10,880 
Nice picture. I look thin.

1114
01:32:13,520 --> 01:32:14,880 
Hey, Lenny!

1115
01:32:16,400 --> 01:32:17,680 
Make him beg.

1116
01:33:37,000 --> 01:33:38,880 
Teddy!

1117
01:33:41,000 --> 01:33:42,120 
Hey, Teddy!

1118
01:33:45,000 --> 01:33:46,680 
Teddy!

1119
01:33:49,800 --> 01:33:51,520 
Jimmy.

1120
01:33:52,000 --> 01:33:55,120 
- What the fuck are you doing here?
- You Jimmy Grants?

1121
01:33:55,200 --> 01:33:57,120 
Expecting any other Jimmys,
memory man?

1122
01:33:57,200 --> 01:34:01,320 
- Do you remember me?
- Yeah, I remember you.

1123
01:34:01,400 --> 01:34:03,680 
Where the fuck's Teddy?

1124
01:34:03,800 --> 01:34:04,800 
Well?

1125
01:34:08,320 --> 01:34:10,120 
Motherfuck!

1126
01:34:10,200 --> 01:34:11,000 
What are you doing?

1127
01:34:13,120 --> 01:34:14,320 
Strip.

1128
01:34:14,400 --> 01:34:16,680 
- You're making a big fucking mistake!
- Strip!

1129
01:34:18,200 --> 01:34:21,200 
My associates are not the kind of people
you wanna piss off.

1130
01:34:21,320 --> 01:34:22,880 
Don't say anything else.

1131
01:34:23,000 --> 01:34:25,800 
- I knew I couldn't trust that fuck!
- Take it off.

1132
01:34:30,880 --> 01:34:32,880 
Your pants, too.

1133
01:34:33,000 --> 01:34:35,400 
- Why?
- I don't wanna get blood on them.

1134
01:34:35,520 --> 01:34:39,320 
Whoa, whoa, whoa! Wait, wait, wait!
Did he tell you what I was bringing?

1135
01:34:39,400 --> 01:34:43,200 
- Take your fuckin' pants off!
- Ive got two hundred grand in the car!

1136
01:34:43,320 --> 01:34:45,800 
- Just take it!
- You think you can bargain with me?

1137
01:34:45,880 --> 01:34:48,120 
- Just take the money and walk away.
- I don't want your fucking money.

1138
01:34:48,200 --> 01:34:50,480 
Then, what?

1139
01:34:50,600 --> 01:34:53,800 
- What do you want from me?
- I want my fucking life back!

1140
01:36:21,520 --> 01:36:22,680 
(softly) Sammy.

1141
01:36:29,200 --> 01:36:31,200 
He said Sammy.
How does he know about Sammy?

1142
01:36:31,320 --> 01:36:33,320 
Oh, fuck.

1143
01:36:52,320 --> 01:36:54,320 
What have I done?

1144
01:36:55,520 --> 01:36:56,680 
Hey, mister! I need help!

1145
01:36:56,800 --> 01:37:00,200 
There's a guy in here, he's hurt bad.
We gotta get him to a doctor.

1146
01:37:00,320 --> 01:37:01,400 
All right.

1147
01:37:02,600 --> 01:37:04,800 
I don't know what happened.
Ive got this memory thing.

1148
01:37:04,880 --> 01:37:07,680 
- Do I know you?
- No. Don't worry, Im a cop.

1149
01:37:07,800 --> 01:37:10,880 
- Is he still breathing?
- Well, I don't know. Maybe.

1150
01:37:11,000 --> 01:37:15,800 
- What the hell were you guys doing?
- I don't remember, I have this condition.

1151
01:37:15,880 --> 01:37:18,800 
I hope it's not as serious as his
cuz this guy's dead.

1152
01:37:19,200 --> 01:37:22,880 
- Ow! Lenny! That shit kills!
- So you remember me now, huh?

1153
01:37:23,000 --> 01:37:27,520 
- You are a fucking cop!
- And Im the guy that helped you find him.

1154
01:37:27,600 --> 01:37:31,880 
- Get up! Get up!
- Lenny, you got the wrong idea!

1155
01:37:34,600 --> 01:37:36,600 
Who is that? He knew me.

1156
01:37:36,680 --> 01:37:39,320 
Of course he did, he raped your wife,
he fucked up your brain.

1157
01:37:39,400 --> 01:37:41,320 
Bullshit! He's not the guy.

1158
01:37:41,400 --> 01:37:45,120 
His name is James F Grants. John G.
Check your tattoos.

1159
01:37:45,200 --> 01:37:47,800 
- Why did he bring two hundred grand?
- What?

1160
01:37:49,680 --> 01:37:51,880 
- What was it for?
- Amphetamines I told him I had.

1161
01:37:52,000 --> 01:37:55,400 
- Is this a drug deal?
- No. Yeah, that and your thing.

1162
01:37:55,520 --> 01:37:58,880 
Look, Jimmy's your guy. I figured
we'd make a few dollars on the side.

1163
01:37:59,000 --> 01:38:01,680 
- How did he know me?
- The Discount Inn.

1164
01:38:01,800 --> 01:38:06,000 
He dealt out of there. The guy at the front
desk let him know if anybody came round.

1165
01:38:06,120 --> 01:38:08,320 
He called Jimmy
the minute he saw you taking a picture.

1166
01:38:08,400 --> 01:38:10,680 
- You're fucking using me.
- No! You get half.

1167
01:38:10,800 --> 01:38:13,120 
He knew about Sammy,
why would I tell him about Sammy?!

1168
01:38:13,200 --> 01:38:16,480 
You tell everybody about Sammy!
Everybody who'll listen!

1169
01:38:16,600 --> 01:38:18,600 
''Remember Sammy Jankis?''
''Remember Sammy Jankis?''

1170
01:38:18,680 --> 01:38:21,520 
Great story.
Gets better every time you tell it.

1171
01:38:21,680 --> 01:38:25,520 
So you lie to yourself to be happy.
There's nothing wrong with that.

1172
01:38:25,600 --> 01:38:29,320 
We all do it. Who cares if there's a few
little details you'd rather not remember?

1173
01:38:30,600 --> 01:38:33,880 
- What the fuck are you talking about?
- I don't know.

1174
01:38:34,000 --> 01:38:38,680 
Your wife surviving the assault.
Her not believing your condition.

1175
01:38:38,800 --> 01:38:42,480 
The torment and pain and anguish
tearing her up inside.

1176
01:38:43,800 --> 01:38:45,000 
The insulin.

1177
01:38:46,320 --> 01:38:48,880 
That's Sammy, not me.
I told you about Sammy.

1178
01:38:49,000 --> 01:38:51,800 
Yeah, right.
Like you tell yourself over and over again.

1179
01:38:51,880 --> 01:38:55,320 
Conditioning yourself to remember,
learning through repetition.

1180
01:38:55,400 --> 01:38:58,120 
Sammy let his wife kill herself.
Sammy ended up in an institution.

1181
01:38:58,200 --> 01:39:01,320 
Sammy was a con man. A faker.

1182
01:39:01,400 --> 01:39:03,520 
I never said that Sammy was faking.

1183
01:39:03,600 --> 01:39:06,320 
You exposed him for what he was.
A fraud.

1184
01:39:06,400 --> 01:39:08,320 
I was wrong. That's the whole point.

1185
01:39:09,520 --> 01:39:12,600 
- See, Sammy's wife came to me...
- Sammy didn't have a wife.

1186
01:39:15,200 --> 01:39:17,880 
It was your wife who had diabetes.

1187
01:39:23,600 --> 01:39:24,480 
Ouch!

1188
01:39:26,600 --> 01:39:28,680 
My wife wasn't diabetic.

1189
01:39:29,400 --> 01:39:31,320 
You sure?

1190
01:39:35,600 --> 01:39:37,520 
Ouch! Cut it out!

1191
01:39:37,600 --> 01:39:39,520 
She wasn't diabetic.

1192
01:39:39,600 --> 01:39:43,200 
You think I don't know my own wife?
What the fuck is wrong with you?

1193
01:39:43,320 --> 01:39:46,320 
I guess I can only make you remember
the things you want to be true.

1194
01:39:46,320 --> 01:39:48,880 
- Like old Jimmy down there.
- He's not the right guy.

1195
01:39:49,000 --> 01:39:51,120 
He was to you.

1196
01:39:51,200 --> 01:39:54,400 
Come on, you got your revenge.
Enjoy it while you still remember.

1197
01:39:54,480 --> 01:39:56,880 
What difference does it make
whether he was your guy or not?

1198
01:39:57,000 --> 01:39:59,000 
- It makes all the difference.
- Why? You're never gonna know.

1199
01:39:59,120 --> 01:40:00,800 
- Yes, I will.
- No, you won't.

1200
01:40:00,880 --> 01:40:03,200 
- Somehow Ill know.
- You won't remember!

1201
01:40:03,320 --> 01:40:04,680 
When it's done, I will know.

1202
01:40:04,800 --> 01:40:07,680 
I thought so, too, I was sure of it,
but you didn't!

1203
01:40:11,320 --> 01:40:16,000 
That's right. The real John G.
I helped you find him over a year ago.

1204
01:40:16,120 --> 01:40:18,880 
- He's already dead.
- Don't lie to me any more.

1205
01:40:19,000 --> 01:40:20,880 
Look, Lenny,...

